243
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:38,468
Oh, no, I can't believe it.

244
00:20:38,683 --> 00:20:44,022
I know. Another year together.
It's gonna be hell.

245
00:20:49,235 --> 00:20:53,398
What's the matter?
I thought you'd be used to failing.

246
00:20:53,656 --> 00:20:58,900
No, you don't understand.
I tried this time. I really tried.

247
00:20:59,162 --> 00:21:00,572
There, there.

248
00:21:00,997 --> 00:21:04,366
This is as good as I can do,
and I still failed.

249
00:21:04,626 --> 00:21:07,580
Well, a 59. It's a high F.

250
00:21:07,837 --> 00:21:12,167
Who am I kidding?
I really am a failure.

251
00:21:12,801 --> 00:21:19,599
Now I know how Washington felt when
he surrendered Fort Necessity in 1754.

252
00:21:19,808 --> 00:21:23,473
You know, 1754.
The famous defeat to the French.

253
00:21:23,729 --> 00:21:26,433
-My God, Bart, you're right!
-So?

254
00:21:26,649 --> 00:21:29,222
You demonstrated applied knowledge.

255
00:21:29,443 --> 00:21:35,563
Such an obscure reference deserves
an extra point. It's only fair.

256
00:21:35,783 --> 00:21:39,282
-You mean I passed?
-Just barely.

257
00:21:39,495 --> 00:21:42,946
I passed. I got a D minus!
I passed!

258
00:21:43,165 --> 00:21:45,123
All right!

259
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:49,540
I passed! I passed! I passed!
I got a D minus!

260
00:21:49,755 --> 00:21:53,171
I got a D minus! I passed!
I got a D minus!

261
00:21:53,384 --> 00:21:55,792
I passed! l--

